==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English [[mummie]], from Old French [[momie]], from Medieval Latin [[mumia]], from Arabic mūmīya, from mūm, ''wax'', from Persian.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌmi|-ʌmi]]

===Noun===
'''mummy''' (''plural:'' '''[[mummies]]''')
# An [[embalm]]ed corpse, especially one prepared for burial by the ancient [[Egyptian]]s.

